
[1]sinister

   SIN'ISTER, a. [L. Probably the primary sense is weak, defective.]

   1. Left; on the left hand, or the side of the left hand; opposed to
   dexter or right; as the sinister cheek; or the sinister side of an
   escutcheon.

   2. Evil; bad; corrupt; perverse; dishonest; as sinister means; sinister
   purpose. He scorns to undermine another's interest by any sinister or
   inferior arts.

   3. Unlucky; inauspicious.

   4. Sinister aspect, in astrology, an appearance of two planets
   happening according to the succession of the signs; as Saturn in Aries,
   and Mars in the same degree of Gemini.
